      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, I think that\u0027s a good strategy. Our current ICC code is (unsurprisingly) incomplete and fairly intertwined with the runtime representation of XYZ and A2B profiles. I do think having an intermediate parsed-ICC representation (eg SkICC) is going to be helpful, for both directions.\n\nOne (minor) issue is that we would need to encode non-ICC data (the blending flag) using a private tag. That\u0027s supported in the format (and we could even register it with ICC so that other people don\u0027t accidentally use the same one), but if we use \u0027skia\u0027, I think we\u0027re probably okay.",
