      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes. At this point, I was just rewriting this so that it would be clear that the code does work with the proposed new color space, although I think your version makes that even clearer. type() is definitely a mess, due to the remaining uses of the derived types (often to use SkGammas), and because we don\u0027t - yet - have a replacement for usage of A2B. This is where I think having a parsed ICC representation is going to be necessary - we need to figure out how the \"pure xform\" library is going to work - how much information do we need extracted from the profile to implement the transformations for complex profiles?",
